#------------------------------------------
# Installing Audiolog
#------------------------------------------

Installing Audiolog is optional. You can run it directly from source now by 
running "python src/audiolog.py".

To check that Audiolog's dependencies are met and to install the "audiolog"
command on your system, run "python setup.py install"

#------------------------------------------
# Audiolog Dependencies
#------------------------------------------

Audiolog leverages many other programs to performs its actions.

These dependencies are used for gathering metadata and are required:
    * Mutagen
    * python-musicbrainz2

These dependencies are necessary for running the graphical interface:
    * Qt
    * PyQt

The rest of the dependencies are optional but will allow Audiolog to do more:
    - Extracting
        * tar
        * unrar
        * unace
        * unzip
    - Converting
        * oggenc (Provided by package "vorbis-tools" in Ubuntu)
        * mpc123
        * mac (No known package, must be compiled)
    - Fingerprint and MusicDNS
        * libofa
        * pyofa
        * libavcodec (FFMPEG)

